<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="mass-n">mass <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /mæs/    美 /mæs/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>团；块；堆：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>mass of</strong> rocks 
一堆石块</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>large <strong>masses of</strong> clouds 
大片的云团</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>许多；大量：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>a mass of / masses of:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve got a mass of things to do this morning. 
今天上午我有许多事要做。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Wherever the Beatles went, masses of fans would welcome them at the airport. 
无论甲壳虫乐队去哪儿，都会有大量的歌迷在机场欢迎他们。</p><footer>译林⑧ – 2</footer></div>

<h4 id="3the-masses">3.<strong>[the masses] 群众；民众：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The trains provide cheap travel for the masses. 
火车给大众提供了便宜的出行方式。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>(物理学) 质量</strong></h4></div>